Name of the Plant: Adenia wightiana  (Wall. ex Wight & Arn.) Engl.

Uses: "Bark is bitter tonic, febrifuge, anthelmintic, galactagogue and used in the form of  tincture for chronic diarrhea, asthma and cardiac troubles. It is used as haemostatic.  Leaves are used in treatment of beri-beri, dropsy and congested liver. Latex is applied  to sores, ulcers, tumours and rheumatic swellings. Ash of the plant is employed as  caustic to open abscesses."

Name of the Plant: Alysicarpus longifolius  (Rottler ex Spreng.) Wight & Arn.
Anogeissus latifolia  (Roxb. ex. DC.) Wall. ex. Guill. &
Asparagus filicinus  Buch.-Ham ex D. Don

Common Name: Marchuba, Paragus, Vilayati Karua, Nakdown, Margiyeh, Halyun

Uses: "Bark is employed in skin troubles. Leaves have antiseptic properties and applied to boils, ulcers and eczema.  Flowers are tonic and stomachic and Berries are purgative and emollient."

Name of the Plant: Canscora diffusa  (Vahl) R.Br. ex. Roem. & Schult.

Uses: "Flowers and pods purgative, febrifugal, astringent, antibilious."
"Dried tuberous roots are aromatic used in diuretic diaphoretic, and astringent properties; used in stomach and bowel complaints."

Name of the Plant: Delphinium denudatum  Wall. ex Hook.f. & Thomson
Euphorbia fusiformis  Buch.-Ham. ex D. Don
Gordonia obtusa  Wall. ex Wight & Arn.
Heteropogon contortus  (L.) P.Beauv. ex Roem. & Schult.
Hygroryza aristata  (Retz.) Nees ex Wight & Arn.
Hypericum uralum  Buch.- Ham. ex D.Don
Ixora nigricans  R.Br. ex Wight & Arn.
Kyllinga nemoralis  (Forst.) Dandy ex Hutcins. & Dalziel
Lobelia nicotianifolia  Roth ex Roem. & Schult.
Sambucus wightiana  Wall. ex Wight & Arn.

Uses: "Both the wood and oil are diuretic, diaphoretic, and expectorant."

Name of the Plant: Seseli diffusum  (Roxb. ex Sm.) Santapau & Wagh
Skimmia laureola  (DC.) Sieb. & Zucc. ex Walp.
Tabernaemontana divaricata  (L.) R.Br. ex Roem. & Schult.

Uses: "Fruits have laxative, stomachic, and tonic properties that form a constituent of triphala, which is an important Ayurvedic medicine"
"Fruits are used for convalescents and they are laxative and easily digestible. Fruits help in controlling cancer like conditions as well."
"Oil is diaphoretic, stimulant used in colic, flatulence, and obstinate vomiting. Affords relief when applied in rheumatism, lumbago, and sprains."
